modules.description: Provides time-related operations such as retrieving the current time, measuring intervals, and handling time deltas. Works with timestamps represented as 64-bit integers and time intervals in nanoseconds. Used to synchronize events in virtualized environments and measure performance in MirageOS-based systems.

Returns the current time as a floating-point number representing seconds since the epoch. Converts a timestamp into a structured time record containing year, month, day, hour, minute, and second fields. Used to retrieve and format system time for logging or timestamping events.
